rn%20trip%20to%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20eventually%20allowed%20to%20board%20after%20proving%20his%20identity%20as%20an%20MP%20and%20presenting%20a%20valid%20visa.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20''It%20was%20stressful%20and%20humiliating%20to%20be%20singled%20out%20in%20such%20an%20aggressive%20way%20by%20immigration%20control%2C%20especially%20when%20travelling%20in%20a%20group%20as%20a%20representative%20of%20the%20British%20Parliament%20on%20long-arranged%20committee%20business.%20While%20I%20don't%20expect%20special%20treatment%20as%20a%20Member%20of%20Parliament%2C%20it%20does%20concern%20me%20that%20had%20I%20not%20been%20an%20MP%2C%20how%20much%20worse%20the%20experience%20might%20have%20been.''%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20incident%2C%20the%20issue%20was%C2%A0raised%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20by%20fellow%20MP%20Clive%20Betts.%C2%A0He%20told%20other%20MPs%20he%20would%20write%20to%20the%20Canadian%20high%20commissioner%20in%20the%20UK%20to%20make%20clear%20the%20%26quot%3Bracist%20and%20Islamophobic%20nature%26quot%3B%20of%20what%20happened%20last%20week%20was%20unacceptable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDeputy%20speaker%20Sir%20Roger%20Gale%20said%20he%20was%20dismayed%20at%20the%20treatment%20of%20the%20MP%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20wholly%20unacceptable%20under%20any%20circumstances.%20But%20it%20is%20particularly%20concerning%2C%20occurring%20as%20it%20did%2C%20in%20the%20course%20of%20official%20travel%20on%20parliamentary%20business.''%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20spokesman%20for%20Air%20Canada%20said%3A%20''Unfortunately%20Mr%20Yasin%20was%20designated%20for%20additional%20screening%20prior%20to%20his%20flight%20after%20a%20security%20check%2C%20but%20he%20was%20still%20able%20to%20travel%20as%20planned%20as%20he%20was%20quickly%20cleared.%20We%20are%20following%20up%20internally%20on%20the%20handling%20of%20this%20particular%20matter%20to%20ensure%20procedures%20were%20properly%20followed%20and%20w