s%2Farticleshow%2F104713137.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Civil%20Servants'%20Authority%20Will%20Be%20Weakened%20if%20They%20Are%20Used%20for%20Poll%20Campaigning%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26083156%2FFu9XIQ-XwAAdeEH.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Constitution%20was%20being%20framed%2C%20there%20were%20concerns%20about%20the%20civil%20services.%20India%E2%80%99s%20home%20minister%20Sardar%20Patel%20had%20famously%20observed%20that%20he%20had%20asked%20his%20secretary%20to%20give%20his%20views%20freely.%20He%20had%20no%20use%20for%20civil%20servants%20who%20wanted%20to%20echo%20the%20views%20of%20the%20political%20masters.%20He%20wanted%20their%20independent%20opinion%20on%20issues%2C%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20governance.%20The%20civil%20services%20were%20thus%20expected%20to%20be%20apolitical.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201970s%20there%20were%20efforts%20to%20dilute%20this%20approach.%20There%20was%20talk%20of%20a%20committed%20civil%20service.%20Questions%20were%20asked%20%E2%80%95%20committed%20to%20whom%3F%20The%20civil%20service%20could%20only%20be%20committed%20to%20the%20Constitution.%20It%20could%20not%20have%20commitments%20in%20favour%20of%20any%20politician%2C%20party%20or%20ideology.%20It%20had%20to%20implement%20policies%20of%20the%20government%20in%20power.%20But%20it%20could%20not%20be%20committed%20to%20their%20political%20ideology%2C%20good%20or%20bad.%20Their%20responsibility%20was%20to%20help%20frame%20policies%20for%20welfare%20and%20economic%20growth%20with%20the%20approval%20of%20ministers%20or%20the%20cabinet.%20They%20were%20expected%20to%20implement%20these%20effectively%20and%20ensure%20that%20people%20got%20the%20full%20benefit%20of%20these%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20achievements%20of%20any%20government%20are%20projected%20through%20the%20media%2C%20for%20which%20the%20publicity%20wings%20of%20the%20government%20are%20specifically%20responsible.%20Political%20masters%20talk%20about%20these%20achievements%20in%20their%20speeches.%20They%20tell%20the%20people%20how%20much%20good%20work%20they%20are%20doing.%20The%20civil%20servants%20only%20explain%20to%20the%20common%20man%20the%20intricacies%20of%20policies%20and%20how%20they%20can%20use%20any%20scheme%20for%20their%20welfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20recent%20media%20reports%20indicate%20that%20a%20large%20body%20of%20civil%20servants%20would%20be%20expected%20to%20tell%20the%20people%20about%20the%20good%20work%20of%20the%20government%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years.%20There%20is%20a%20campaign%20mode%20being%20prescribed%20for%20this.%20This%20is%20very%20unfortunate.%20Whether%20the%20government%20has%20done%20well%20or%20badly%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years%20is%20not%20for%20them%20to%20say.%20They%20can%20only%20describe%20policies%20in%20their%20sectors.%20This%20approach%20may%20appear%20to%20be%20a%20politicisation%20of%20bureaucracy%2C%20which%20is%20very%20unfortunate.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20another%20aspect%20of%20this%20issue.%20Governments%20in%20different%20states%20are%20run%20by%20different%20political%20parties.%20Many%20states%20have%20their%20own%20schemes.%20During%20elections%2C%20states%20ruled%20by%20parties%20opposed%20to%20the%20Centre%20may%20like%20to%20propagate%20their%20own%20policies.%20They%20may%20like%20to%20tell%20people%20how%20badly%20the%20Centre%20is%20doing%20and%20how%20well%20they%20themselves%20are%20working.%20This%20would%20create%20problems%20in%20implementing%20the%20idea%20of%20projecting%20achievements.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20important%20issue%20involved%20here%20is%20our%20long%20term-view%20of%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20civil%20service.%20While%20the%20campaign%20planned%20may%20give%20some%20benefits%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20it%20may%20open%20the%20door%20to%20a%20civil%20service%20of%20poor%20quality.%20The%20essence%20of%20a%20democracy%20and%20good%20governance%20is%20that%20civil%20servants%20try%20to%20improve%20their%20professionalism%20in%20framing%20policies%20and%20ensuring%20maximum%20benefits%20to%20the%20people.%20They%20specialise%20in%20effectively%20implementing%20government%20policies%20to%20ensure%20maximum%20benefits%20to%20people.%20Whether%20an%20approach%20or%20programme%20is%20superior%20or%20inferior%20to%20the%20earlier%20government%E2%80%99s%20is%20not%20their%20business.%20But%20now%2C%20they%20are%20being%20effectively%20called%20upon%20to%20identify%20with%20one%20government.%20This%20is%20not%20part%20of%20the%20parliamentary%20system%20of%20governance.%20Governments%20come%20and%20go%20but%20the%20civil%20servants%20remain%20a%20neutral%20observer.%20The%20current%20orders%20of%20the%20government%20are%20completely%20in%20violation%20of%20this%20spirit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20on%20this%20issue%20is%20difficult%20to%20understand%20in%20view%20of%20the%20ongoing%20election%20process%2C%20during%20which%20the%20state%20machinery%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20completely%20neutral.%20To%20argue%20that%20those%20representatives%20of%20the%20Centre%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20disseminate%20achievements%20of%20the%20party%20in%20power%20is%20clearly%20unfair.%20The%20Election%20Commission%20may%20take%20note%20of%20it%20and%20review%20this%20programme%20for%20poll-bound%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EB.K.%20Chaturvedi%20is%20former%20Cabinet%20Secretary%20and%20member%2C%20Planning%20Commission.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698289366000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26083156%2FFu9XIQ-XwAAdeEH.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcivil-servants-authority-will-be-weakened-if-they-are-used-for-poll-campaigning%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Whether%20the%20government%20has%20done%20well%20or%20badly%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years%20is%20not%20for%20civil%20servants%20to%20say.%20They%20can%20only%20describe%20policies%20in%20their%20sectors.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcivil-servants-authority-will-be-weakened-if-they-are-used-for-poll-campaigning%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20new%20bill%20in%20Congress%20could%20wipe%20out%20the%20credit%20card%20rewards%20programs%20Americans%20rely%20on%20for%20their%20vacations%2C%20Southwest%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Southwest%20Airlines%20plane%20takes%20off%2C%20Sen.%20Dick%20Durbin%20speaks%20at%20a%20hearing%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539d26f96f7540cd06624d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAirlines%20like%20Southwest%20have%20been%20criticizing%20the%20Credit%20Card%20Competition%20Act%2C%20which%20they%20say%20would%20kill%20loyalty%20rewards%20programs.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%20and%20Chip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESouthwest%20Airlines%20said%20a%20new%20bill%20in%20Congress%20could%C2%A0%26quot%3Bcompletely%20end%26quot%3B%20loyalty%20rewards%20programs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20taking%20aim%20at%20the%20Credit%20Card%20Competition%20Act%2C%20which%20seeks%20to%20lower%20credit%20card%20fees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAirlines%20like%20Southwest%20say%20the%20bill%20cuts%20funds%20from%20payment%20networks%2C%20who'd%20be%20less%20willing%20to%20offer%20rewards.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESouthwest%20Airlines%20has%20come%20out%20swinging%20against%20a%20new%20congressional%20bill%20that%20hopes%20to%20lower%20credit%20card%20transaction%20fees%2C%20saying%20it%20could%20kill%20flyer%20miles%20programs%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2F118%2Fbills%2Fs1838%2FBILLS-118s1838is.xml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECredit%20Card%20Competition%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20introduced%20by%20Sen.%20Dick%20Durbin%20of%20Illinois%20in%20June%2C%20aims%20to%20require%20big%20US%20banks%20to%20give%20businesses%20a%20choice%20of%20at%20least%20one%20payment%20network%20that%20isn't%20Visa%20or%20Mastercard%20in%20credit%20card%20transactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurbin%20said%20Visa%20and%20Mastercard%20hold%20a%20duopoly%20over%20card%20payments%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20control%20over%2080%25%20of%20such%20transactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20charge%20swipe%20fees%20of%20around%203%25%2C%20which%20businesses%20often%20pass%20on%20to%20consumers%20by%20hiking%20prices%2C%20and%20Durbin%20hopes%20that%20his%20bill%20will%20lower%20the%20fees%20by%20introducing%20market%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESouthwest%2C%20however%2C%20criticized%20the%20bill%20as%20%26quot%3Bbad%20policy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSouthwest%20strongly%20opposes%20the%20CCCA%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20airline%20told%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BOur%20customers%20and%20employees%20use%20the%20Southwest%20Rapid%20Rewards%20Credit%20Card%20to%20earn%20points%20that%20can%20be%20redeemed%20for%20Southwest%20flights%2C%20car%20rentals%2C%20gift%20cards%2C%20and%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20legislation%20is%20bad%20policy%20and%20would%20undermine%2C%20if%20not%20completely%20end%2C%20credit%20card%20rewards%20programs%20that%20millions%20of%20Americans%20rely%20on%20for%20their%20vacations%20or%20personal%20travel%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20Southwest%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20argument%20from%20airlines%20like%20Southwest%20is%20that%20Durbin's%20bill%20would%20significantly%20cut%20revenues%20for%20payment%20networks%20like%20Visa%20and%20Mastercard%2C%20and%20that%20those%20networks%20would%20be%20less%20incentivized%20to%20offer%20lucrative%20loyalty%20rewards%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20end%20of%20flyer%20miles%20and%20points%20programs%20would%20significantly%20slash%20revenues%20for%20airlines%2C%20which%20earn%20billions%20from%20partnerships%20with%20credit%20card%20issuers.%20They're%20typically%20paid%20whenever%20a%20consumer%20uses%20one%20of%20their%20co-branded%20cards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Kirby%2C%20CEO%20of%20United%20Airlines%2C%20also%20blasted%20the%20bill%20in%20an%20October%2018%20earnings%20call%2C%20saying%20it%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcongress-billcredit-card-fees-kill-flier-miles-united-scott-kirby-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bkill%26quot%3B%20rewards%20programs.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B84%25%20of%20US%20consumers%20have%20some%20kind%20of%20rewards%20card%20in%20their%20wallet.%20I%20bet%20almost%20everyone%20in%20this%20call%20has%20one%2C%20and%20they%20like%20them%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOur%20customers%20certainly%20like%20them%20a%20lot.%20And%20so%20I%20think%20it'd%20be%20hard%20in%20Congress%20to%20take%20a%20vote%20that%2084%25%20of%20your%20voters%20are%20going%20to%20be%20upset%20with%20the%20outcome%20of%20that%20vote.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Credit%20Card%20Competition%20Act%20was%20originally%20introduced%20to%20the%20previous%20Congress%20in%202022%2C%20but%20never%20came%20to%20a%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurbin%20has%20now%20re-introduced%20the%20bill%2C%20and%20it's%20picking%20up%20bipartisan%20support%20with%20three%20co-sponsors%20in%20the%20Senate%20from%20both%20the%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20parties.%20In%20the%20House%2C%20GOP%20Rep.%20Lance%20Gooden%20of%20Texas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F118th-congress%2Fhouse-bill%2F3881%2Fcosponsors%3Fs%3D1%26r%3D1%26q%3D%257B%2522search%2522%253A%255B%2522chamberActionDateTotal%253A%255C%25222023-06-07%257C118%257Cintroduced%255C%2522%2BAND%2BbillIsReserved%253A%255C%2522N%255C%2522%2522%255D%257D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintroduced%20the%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20seven%20co-sponsors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20to%20comment%20on%20airlines'%20criticism%20of%20his%20bill%2C%20Durbin%20told%20Insider%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20rich%20that%20the%20airline%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20which%20generates%20billions%20of%20dollars%20each%20year%20from%20co-branded%20credit%20cards%20%E2%80%94%20is%20pretending%20to%20have%20hardworking%20Americans'%20interest%20at%20heart.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20airlines%20have%20negotiated%20sweet%20heart%20deals%20with%20the%20biggest%20Wall%20Street%20banks%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20consumers%20and%20local%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurbin%20pointed%20to%20the%20European%20Union's%20policies%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-eu-antitrust-payment-idUSKBN240293%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elimit%20payment%20networks%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20charging%20more%20than%200.3%25%20in%20transaction%20fees.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20banks%20and%20airlines%20still%20offer%20points%20and%20miles%20programs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-cards-congress-competition-act-rewards-wipe-out-southwest-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698288901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539d26f96f7540cd06624d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-cards-congress-competition-act-rewards-wipe-out-southwest-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Southwest%20blasted%20the%20Credit%20Card%20Competition%20Act%2C%20saying%20it%20would%20%26quot%3Bundermine%2C%20if%20not%20completely%20end%26quot%3B%20credit%20card%20rewards%20programs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40insider.com%20(Matt