his%20second%20and%20final%20day%20of%20testimony%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-ny-fraud-trial-opens-today-heres-why-still-matters-2023-9%5C%22%3ETrump's%20ongoing%20civil%20fraud%20trial%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20despite%20getting%20grilled%20about%20his%20previous%20lies%20and%20about%20how%2C%20after%20decades%20in%20Trump's%20inner%20circle%2C%20he%20never%20got%20a%20job%20in%20the%20Trump%20White%20House%20and%20now%20makes%20a%20living%20writing%20anti-Trump%20books%20and%20hosting%20a%20podcast%20attacking%20the%20former%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20thought%20you%20were%20going%20to%20be%20named%20chief%20of%20staff%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20Trump%20White%20House%2C%20firebrand%20defense%20lawyer%20Alina%20Habba%20told%20Cohen%20at%20one%20point%2C%20her%20voice%20accusatory%20and%20loud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20I%20did%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20protested%20from%20the%20witness%20stand%2C%20in%20one%20of%20the%20rare%20moments%20that%20his%20voice%20rose%20to%20meet%20Habba's%20volume.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20joke%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20despite%20a%202017%20text%20chain%20in%20which%20he%20bragged%20he'd%20get%20the%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20made%20a%20career%20out%20of%20publically%20attacking%20President%20Trump%20haven't%20you%3F%26quot%3B%20Habba%20asked%20at%20another%20point.%20Cohen%20paused%20before%20evenly%20responding%2C%20%26quot%3BYes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohen's%20life%20as%20Trump's%20nemesis-in-chief%20is%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20that%20of%20the%20young%20man%20who%20once%20so%20admired%20Trump%20he%20read%20%26quot%3BThe%20Art%20of%20the%20Deal%26quot%3B%20twice.%20%26quot%3BIn%20college%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20testified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20once%20stated%20that%20you%20would%20take%20a%20bullet%20for%20President%20Trump%2C%26quot%3B%20Habba%20reminded%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVanity%20Fair%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20answered%20with%20a%20smile%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20magazine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fnews%2F2017%2F09%2Fmichael-cohen-interview-donald-trump%5C%22%3Ewhere%20his%20%26quot%3Btake%20a%20bullet%26quot%3B%20quote%20was%20first%20printed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20back%20in%202017.%20%26quot%3BEmily%20Fox%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20sounding%20almost%20wistful%20as%20he%20named%20the%20story's%20author%2C%20Emily%20Jane%20Fox.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20both%20days%20he%20testified%2C%20Cohen%20sat%20some%2020%20feet%20from%20the%20defense%20table%20and%20Trump%2C%20who%20watched%20the%20testimony%20of%20his%20fixer-turned-foe%20on%20Tuesday%20and%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohen's%20time%20in%20the%20trial%20spotlight%20started%20with%20a%20bombshell.%20Early%20in%20direct%20examination%20Tuesday%2C%20Cohen%20testified%20that%20for%20years%2C%20he%20inflated%20Trump's%20net%20worth%20for%20official%20banking%20documents%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-cohen-ny-fraud-trial-cage-match-its-on-2023-10%5C%22%3Eto%20hit%20a%20number%20Trump%20had%20%26quot%3Barbitrarily%26quot%3B%20picked.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20remarkable%20piece%20of%20testimony.%20And%20it%20fed%20directly%20into%20the%20fraud%20narrative%20of%20New%20York%20Attorney%20General%20Letitia%20James%2C%20whose%20lawsuit%20prompted%20the%20ongoing%20trial%2C%20now%20in%20its%20fourth%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20has%20accused%20Trump%20of%20routinely%20and%20fraudulently%20inflating%20his%20net%20worth%20by%20billions%20of%20dollars%20a%20year%20to%20mislead%20lenders%20and%20insurers.%20She%20is%20seeking%20to%20permanently%20ban%20Trump%20and%20four%20longtime%20Trump%20Organization%20executives%2C%20including%20his%20two%20eldest%20sons%2C%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20Jr.%2C%20and%20Eric%20Trump%2C%20from%20ever%20doing%20business%20in%20New%20York%20again.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20Cohen's%202019%20testimony%20before%20Congress%20that%20first%20exposed%20what%20the%20trial%20judge%2C%20New%20York%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Arthur%20Engoron%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-new-york-judge-finds-business-2023-9%5C%22%3Ehas%20already%20ruled%20was%20rampant%20net-worth%20fraud.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Cohen's%20two%20days%20on%20the%20stand%2C%20through%20no%20fault%20of%20his%20own%2C%20went%20from%20fireworks%20to%20fizzle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20day's%20end%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Trump's%20attorneys%20unsuccessfully%20demanded%20an%20immediate%20verdict%2C%20claiming%20that%20Habba%20had%20trapped%20Cohen%20into%20contradicting%20himself%20by%20admitting%2C%20during%20cross%2C%20that%20Trump%20never%20directly%20ordered%20his%20net%20worth%20be%20fudged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20state's%20key%20witness%2C%20who%20they%20base%20their%20entire%20case%20on%2C%20has%20now%20testified%20that%20Mr.%20Trump%20and%20Mr.%20Weisselberg%20did%20not%20direct%20him%20to%20inflate%20the%20numbers%2C%26quot%3B%20complained%20Clifford%20Robert%2C%20an%20attorney%20for%20Eric%20Trump%20and%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20Jr.%2C%20who%20are%20both%20defendants%20in%20the%20attorney%20general's%20case.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20government's%20key%20witnesses%20has%20fallen%20flat%20on%20his%20face%2C%26quot%3B%20Robert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Trump%20didn't%20have%20to%20specifically%20order%20anything%2C%20Cohen%20explained%20during%20re-direct%20examination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDonald%20Trump%20speaks%20like%20a%20mob%20boss%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20explained%20on%20re-direct%20testimony%20by%20an%20assistant%20district%20attorney%2C%20Colleen%20Faherty.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20what%20he%20does%20is%2C%20he%20tells%20you%20what%20he%20wants%20without%20specifically%20telling%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20when%20he%20said%20to%20me%2C%20'I'm%20worth%20more%20than%20five%20million.%20I'm%20actually%20worth%20maybe%20six%2C%20maybe%20seven%2C%20could%20be%20eight%2C'%20we%20understood%20what%20he%20wanted.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDenied%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said%20of%20the%20defense's%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20verdict%26quot%3B%20bid.%20Soon%20afterward%2C%20Trump%20rose%20from%20his%20seat%20and%20left%20the%20courtroom%2C%20trailed%20by%20nearly%20a%20dozen%20Secret%20Service%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20rejecting%20the%20defense%20request%20for%20an%20early%20verdict%20in%20their%20favor%2C%20the%20judge%20explained%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bhas%20evidence%2C%20credible%20or%20not%2C%20all%20over%20the%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20%26quot%3Benough%20evidence%20in%20this%20case%20to%20fill%20this%20courtroom%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20fraud%20lawsuit%20that%20led%20to%20the%20trial%20is%20alone%20more%20than%20200%20pages%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20way%2C%20no%20how%20this%20case%20is%20being%20dismissed%20because%20of%20an%20equivocal%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3Earguably%3C%2Fem%3E%20equivocal%20%E2%80%93%20statement%20by%20one%20witness%20who%20I%20don't%20consider%20the%20key%20witness%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20Cohen's%20testimony%2C%20already%20maligned%20as%20less%20than%20key%2C%20was%20overshadowed%20Wednesday%20by%20a%20far%20flashier%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20after%20the%20lunch%20break%2C%C2%A0%20Trump%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-takes-stand-after-violating-fraud-trial-gag-order-2023-10%5C%22%3Esuddenly%20summoned%20to%20take%20the%20witness%20stand%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20judge.%20Trump%20was%20asked%20whether%20he'd%20just%20called%20the%20judge's%20law%20clerk%20%26quot%3Bpartisan%26quot%3B%20in%20front%20of%20reporters%2C%20thereby%20violating%20a%20partial%20gag%20order%20banning%20attacks%20on%20the%20judge's%20court%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngoron%20found%20Trump's%20testimony%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20he%20swore%20un