0small%2C%20warm-blooded%20animals%20like%20mice%2C%26quot%3B%20Jay%20Storz%2C%20a%20biologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nebraska%E2%80%94Lincoln%2C%20who%20led%20a%20study%20of%20the%20mouse%20mummies%2C%20told%20Insider%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-mummy-discovered-egypt-gold-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emummies%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20leaf-eared%20mice%2C%20which%20are%20known%20to%20live%20at%20high%20elevations.%20But%20warm-blooded%20life%20at%2020%2C000%20feet%20is%20unheard%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22fat%20brown%20mouse%20with%20large%20round%20ears%20stands%20on%20the%20fingers%20of%20a%20white%20gloved%20hand%20against%20a%20red-brown%20mountaintop%20landscape%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65380f1296f7540cd0644a67%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20leaf-eared%20mouse.%20The%20species%20is%20known%20to%20live%20at%20high%20elevations%2C%20but%20baffled%20scientists%20at%20more%20than%2020%2C000%20feet.%3Cp%3EMarcial%20Quiroga-Carmona%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20extreme%20elevations%20were%20previously%20assumed%20to%20be%20completely%20uninhabitable%20by%20mammals%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mummies%20suggest%20these%20mice%20have%20been%20reaching%20outlandish%20heights%20for%20centuries%20or%20longer%2C%20according%20to%20Storz%2C%20since%20this%20species%20%26quot%3Bhas%20inhabited%20the%20high%20Andes%20for%20many%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Storz%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they%20could%20have%20been%20frequenting%20the%20volcano%20summits%20for%20quite%20some%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20seem%20to%20still%20be%20living%20there%20in%20small%20numbers.%20The%20research%20team%20found%20a%20living%20mouse%20at%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmount-everest-death-zone-what-happens-to-body-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20altitudes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20evidence%20of%20active%20burrows%2C%20Storz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20still%20a%20lot%20left%20to%20discover%2C%26quot%3B%20Storz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20live%20mouse%20and%20the%20summit%20mummies%20%26quot%3Brepresent%20the%20highest%20altitude%20physical%20records%20of%20mammals%20in%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fcurrent-biology%2Ffulltext%2FS0960-9822(23)01161-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20published%20Monday%20in%20the%20journal%20Current%20Biology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECould%20these%20mice%20have%20special%20adaptations%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStorz%20stumbled%20upon%20the%20first%20mouse%20mummy%20by%20chance.%20Soon%20he%20and%20his%20colleagues%20were%20finding%20more%20and%20more%20freeze-dried%20mouse%20cadavers%20in%20the%20crevices%20of%20volcanic%20rock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22man%20in%20yellow%20windbreaker%20jacket%20and%20grey%20wide%20brimmed%20hat%20reaches%20a%20trekking%20pole%20into%20a%20crevice%20under%20a%20rock%20outcropping%20atop%20a%20barren%20mountain%20landscape%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6538131396f7540cd064531e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJay%20Storz%20excavates%20mouse%20mummies%20on%20the%20summit%20of%20Volc%C3%A1n%20P%C3%BAlar%20in%20northern%20Chile.%3Cp%3EMario%20P%C3%A9rez%20Mamani%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mummies%20were%20mostly%20a%20few%20decades%20old%2C%20but%20some%20dated%20back%20several%20centuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenomic%20analysis%20of%20the%20mummies%20showed%20that%20they%20were%20equal%20numbers%20of%20male%20and%20female%20mice%20and%20that%20some%20were%20closely%20related.%20That%20suggests%20the%20mice%20actually%20established%20communities%20at%20the%20tops%20of%20the%20volcanoes%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20few%20individuals%20randomly%20climbing%20up%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStorz%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20only%20advantage%20he%20can%20think%20of%20for%20the%20mountaineering%20mice%20is%20that%20there%20are%20no%20predators%20on%20top%20of%20the%20volcanoes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20mice's%20motives%2C%20it's%20a%20mystery%20how%20they%20manage%20to%20survive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWell-trained%20mountain%20climbers%20can%20tolerate%20such%20extreme%20elevations%20during%20a%20one-day%20summit%20attempt%2C%20but%20the%20fact%20that%20mice%20are%20actually%20living%20at%20such%20elevations%20demonstrates%20that%20we%20have%20underestimated%20the%20physiological%20tolerances%20of%20small%20mammals%2C%26quot%3B%20Storz%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F1005132%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20comparing%20the%20summit%20environment%20to%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20are%20now%20looking%20for%20signs%20of%20physiological%20adaptations%20that%20may%20allow%20these%20mice%20to%20survive%20at%20high%20elevations%20with%20low%20oxygen%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20collected%20mice%20from%20different%20elevations%20and%20are%20now%20experimentally%20exposing%20them%20to%20low%20oxygen%20to%20see%20whether%20the%20extreme-altitude%20mice%20show%20any%20unique%20physiology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStorz's%20team%20is%20also%20continuing%20to%20search%20the%20volcano%20tops%20for%20signs%20of%20mice%2C%20living%20or%20mummified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20it's%20the%20top%20of%20the%20highest%20mountains%20or%20the%20darkest%20depths%20of%20the%20ocean%2C%20it%20is%20always%20exciting%20to%20discover%20animals%20living%20in%20places%20where%20nobody%20expects%20anything%20to%20be%20living%2C%26quot%3B%20Storz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmummified-mice-mars-like-volcano-stump-scientists-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698276659000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65380d6496f7540cd0644836%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmummified-mice-mars-like-volcano-stump-scientists-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20tops%20of%2020%2C000-foot%20volcanoes%20were%20thought%20to%20be%20uninhabitable%2C%20until%20baffled%20scientists%20started%20finding%20freeze-dried%20mouse%20mummies%20there.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis%2CMorgan%20McFall-Johnsen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A138%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmummified-mice-mars-like-volcano-stump-scientists-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Researchers%20discovered%20a%20hidden%20Antarctic%20landscape%20under%20a%20layer%20of%20ice%20over%20a%20mile%20thick%20that%20shows%20how%20different%20the%20continent%20looked%20millions%20of%20years%20ago%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221998%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20small%20boat%20in%20the%20water%20near%20the%20Admiralty%20Mountains%20in%20the%20east%20of%20Antarctica%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65385350356802a56be2f155%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221498%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Admiralty%20Mountains%20loom%20in%20eastern%20Antarctica.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Peacock%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EResearchers%20recently%20found%20an%20%26quot%3Bundiscovered%20landscape%26quot%3B%20beneath%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2FAntarctica-ice-shelf-previously-thought-stable-collapses-2022-3%5C%22%3EAntarctica's%20ice%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20continent%20once%20looked%20very%20different%20and%20was%20much%20warmer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EResearchers%20are%20eager%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20Antarctica's%20past%2C%20especially%20since%20its%20ice%20is%20melting.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMillions%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20Antarctica%20looked%20very%20different.%20Instead%20of%20a%20mostly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fantarctica-lost-enough-ice-cover-us-three-feet-water-2023-10%5C%22%3Eice-covered%20continent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20was%20a%20landmass%20with%20free-flowing%20rivers%20and%20glacier-carved%20valleys.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20between%2014%20million%20and%2034%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmelting-glaciers-ice-sheets-sea-level-rise-climate-disaster-2022-12%5C%22%3Eice%20sheet%3C%2Fa%3E%20crept%20across%20the%20continent.%20It%20locked%20some%20of%20the%20lush%20landscape%20beneath%20over%20a%20mile%20of%20ice%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fscience%2Fscience-news%2Fancient-landscape-formed-rivers-revealed-deep-antarctic-ice-rcna121981%5C%22%3ENBC%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20landscape%20remained%20hidden%20for%20millennia%20until%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20an%20undiscovered%20landscape%2C%26quot%3B%20glaciologist%20Stewart%20Jamieson%20and%20lead%20author%20of%20a%20study%20on%20the%20new%20discovery%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fnews%2F2023-10-frozen-landscape-antarctic-ice.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Agence%20France-Presse%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one's%20laid%20eyes%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETropical%20%3Cstrong%3EAntarctic%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJamieson%20and%20his%20fellow%20researchers%20looked%20at%20an%20area%20of%20the%20continent%20that%20was%20about%2012%2C000%20square%20miles%20wide%2C%20a%20little%20smaller%20than%20the%20state%20of%20Maryland%2C%20and%20located%20about%20186%20miles%20inland%20from%20the%20Eastern%20Antarctic%20coast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ancient%2C%20slow-moving%20ice%20eroded%20much%20of%20Antarctica's%20features.%20However%2C%20in%20this%20region%2C%20the%20ice%20wasn't%20thick%20enough%20to%20do%20the%20same%20damage.%20Instead%2C%20the%20ice%20may%20have%20helped%20preserve%20the%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuddenly%2C%20that%20landscape%20is%20frozen%20in%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Jamieson%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fplanet-earth%2Fantarctica%2Fghost-of-ancient-river-carved-landscape-discovered-beneath-antarctica%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELive%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20findings%20were%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D547523c18863854bed0b6bb3e0aa9888d88ae45aa6a9ca19083a4dc992cc2fa4%26postID%3D65385201b5f87e160e0f9c5c%26postSlug%3Dwhat-is-underneath-antarctica-land-hills-valley-2023-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41467-023-42152-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENature%20Communications%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJamieson%20and%20his%20colleagues%20looked%20at%20previously%20collected%20satellite%20images%20and%20radio-echo%20sounding%20data%20from%20East%20Antarctica.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERES%20is%20a%20technique%20that%20uses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmystery-radio-waves-unknown-object-milky-way-center-2021-10%5C%22%3Eradio%20waves%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20determine%20the%20thickness%20of%20ice.%20This%20helped%20the%20researchers%20determine%20the%20height%20of%20peaks%20and%20depths%20of%20valleys%20that%20lay%20hidden%20beneath%20the%20ice.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3